column271: should just let people rate all 50 on one page it would be waaaaaay faster and less boring.
Thanks!  I didn't have any problems.
Thank you for letting me participate.

I did have at least one skip -- I saw the box was checked after I hit the send button -- that didn't apply.  On the non-technical side, I found it difficult to define my culture's values as a whole on many of the concepts, as there are differences between what we see in news and entertainment media, what people say about themselves and others in private, and what those same people actually do in their day to day lives.  Almost nothing is truly neutral to everyone I know; most of the neutrals marked just show where the positives and negatives cancel out.  All in all, this was quite interesting.
Some of the sliders took several tries as they would get stuck.
very unique and actually interesting/thought provoking about my beliefs and underlying values. an mturk hit rarity, thanks.
I think 'Extremely' should be the highest level on each end - it is in my mind. 'Infinitely' seems way dramatic.
